result.execSummary:
The defendant David A. Newling was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Sex Offender - Fail/Update Information, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 301.45(4)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: The Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol or drugs unless prescribed by a physician.  The Defendant must reside in an alcohol or drug free environment.  The Defendant is to obtain and maintain full time employment and/or educational programming as recommended.  The Defendant is to have no unsupervised contact with any children under 16 years of age except for his own children or any children approved by the Agent.  The Defendant is to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  The Defendant is not to go into any bars, taverns or businesses where the primary purpose is to sell alcohol.  The Defendant cannot work in any profession which would involve working with children under 16 years of age.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due, and/or other collection means, such as income assignment will be issued.

Stayed.  To be used by the Agent for probation violations.
**AMENDED 1/18/16 Stay lifted. Defendant to serve 9 months.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to any other sentence now serving.

superMiscConds.notes: The Defendant is to undergo any counseling the agent finds appropriate and must comply with any recommended treatment/assessment/counseling.  Defendant may not withdraw from any ordered program without permission of the agent and/or provider.  The Defendant is to comply with sex offender registry.
